==English==
===Etymology===
[[barley]] + [[corn]]

===Noun===
'''barleycorn'''
# a [[grain]] of [[barley]]
# (''British, obsolete'')the [[length]] of such a grain; a unit of length of approximately one third (or sometimes one quarter) of an [[inch]] or 8mm.
# (''architecture. woodworking'') a small groove between two [[moulding]]s
# In English tradition [[John Barleycorn]] personifies [[beer]] and [[whisky]] which are produced from [[malt]] a product of [[barley]].